      },
      "date": "2017-02-03 23:50:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI'm struggling to see what part of this patch is actually fixing the problem.  AFAICS, 'i' isn't used after the first loop before being reset, and the added check for ':' would only break out of the \"multiple NID\" loop early and move to the second \"failover NID\" loop.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "49f35cbb0eaa8f76ac54c503ccbf45a4b4a133a7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 103,
        "name": "Zhenyu Xu",
        "email": "bobijam@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bobijam"
      },
      "date": "2017-02-06 05:39:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n',' is used to define multiple nids of a single mgs node, while ':' is used to separate different mgs node. So the ':' break in this patch would add multiple nids to associate with the primary mgs node's uuid; while the old code only associate the first one nid with the primary mgs, but add the remaining nids of the primary mgs to the failover mgs node in error.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "ed92d2bd863732371ac66fe8bfe51295639c6bc9",
      "author": {
